ts** - Cannot compile without `labels`, `runtimev1alpha1`, `errors`\n3. **Informer infrastructure incomplete** - Missing 5+ critical files\n4. **Factory struct conflict** - `sharedInformerFactory` definition issues\n\n---\n\n## Recommendations\n\n### P0 - Fix Build Errors\n\n1. **Fix `scheme/register.go`**:\n   - Replace `serializer.NewCodecGroup(Scheme)` with proper serializer setup\n   - Fix `SchemeBuilder` usage to use `runtime.NewSchemeBuilder()`\n\n2. **Fix listers imports**:\n   - Add missing imports to `agentruntime.go` and `codeinterpreter.go`\n\n3. **Generate missing informer files**:\n   - Run `make gen-client` or `hack/update-codegen.sh` to generate:\n     - `informers/externalversions/runtime/interface.go`\n     - `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/interface.go`\n     - `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime.go`\n     - `informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go`\n     - `informers/externalversions/generic.go`\n\n4. **Fix factory.go**:\n   - Add missing imports (`time`, `fmt`, `runtimev1alpha1`)\n   - Resolve struct definition conflict\n\n### P1 - Complete Verification\n\n5. Verify fake client implementations match interface contracts\n6. Add integration tests for client-go\n7. Verify code generation script works end-to-end\n\n---\n\n## Conclusion\n\nThe **API contracts and interface definitions are correctly implemented** according to the spec. However, the implementation has **critical build errors** that prevent compilation:\n\n- Core typed clients: ✅ Spec compliant\n- Scheme registration: ❌ Broken\n- Listers: ❌ Missing imports\n- Informers: ❌ Incomplete (missing files)\n\n**Cannot pass quality gate until build errors are resolved.**\n\n---\n\n**Verification Date**: 2026-04-11\n**Verifier**: opencode\n**Spec Version**: deployment/client-go.md\n**Next Steps**: Fix P0 build errors, regenerate missing informer code\n","additions":9,"deletions":0},"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_ba